    <sect1>
        <title>Installing &daps;</title>
        <para>Install &daps; as shown in the following procedure:</para>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para> Open Yast</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para> Click on <guilabel>Software Management</guilabel></para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para> Go to the <guilabel>Search</guilabel> tab.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para> Search for "daps"</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para> Install "daps" and "daps-docmanager</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title>Creating new Projects</title>
        <para>Use the steps in the bottom to create a new project. You will see all functions to
            create a new project with the command:</para>
        <screen>daps init --help</screen>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para>Open you search tool with Alt+F2. Search for console.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Open the console</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Create a directory with the name "dapstest" for example.</para>
                <screen>
                    $ mkdir YOUR_PATH/dapstest 
                </screen>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Enter the command:</para>
                <screen>$ daps --basedir=YOUR_PATH/dapstest --envfile=ENV-test-daps init</screen>
                <para>You have been created a daps directory</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title>Building Formatts</title>
        <para>In the following points you will see the procedure of transforming formats into a
            other format. For example: XML into PDF. </para>
        <sect2>
            <title>Transforming XML into PDF</title>
            <para> To transform XML into PDF, use the following steps:</para>
            <procedure>
                <step>
                    <para> Open your Search tool with Alt+F2. Type into this line: console.</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Open the console</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Create a ENV Data. With the command: </para>
                    <screen>$ touch YOUR_PATH/dapsdirectory/ENV-YOUR-DATA</screen>
                    <para>You need a daps directory. Look at creating new project.</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Write in this data the following text: </para>
                    <screen>
MAIN=ENTER-THE-NAME-OF-YOUR-XML-DATA.xml
DISTVER=1.0

export DAPS_ENV_NAME=$(basename $BASH_SOURCE)</screen>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Save this data.</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para> Enter in your console:</para>
                    <screen>$ daps -e ENV_DATA pdf</screen>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para> Finish. Your .xml file is now a .pdf file.</para>
                </step>
            </procedure>
            <para> if you want a other format, change the word pdf into txt, epub, wiki or man. More
                options can you see with the command: "daps --help"</para>
        </sect2>
